man organization prepares refugees to care for the elderly The issue "is a vicious spiral" for elderly people who already have health problems since loneliness can increase the likelihood of depression or cardiovascular disease, Maike Luhmann, a psychology professor who headed the study, told Bild. On Wednesday, British Prime Minister Theresa May appointed a "Minister for Loneliness" to focus on providing "practical and emotional support" for the elderly as well as young disabled people. "For far too many people, loneliness is the sad reality of modern life," May said. Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
